{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_11_connectivity", "label": "north-star 11 - local input + mixing", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\11-connectivity.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The block-local slice scheme = grouped/depthwise-separable convolution; you MUST mix; cheaper mixing via channel-shuffle, butterfly/Monarch, or MoE routing; validated by MLP-Mixer."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_11_connectivity_depthwise_separable_conv", "label": "Grouped / depthwise-separable convolution", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\11-connectivity.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The author's block-local slice scheme (Ganglion=depthwise/grouped, translate clip=pointwise 1x1 mix) IS depthwise-separable convolution (MobileNet/Xception); a gx reduction in weights/compute and crossbar area, block-diagonal gradients make credit block-local (easier on-chip)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_11_connectivity_channel_shuffle", "label": "Channel shuffle (ShuffleNet)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\11-connectivity.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Mix groups by a fixed permutation (free routing on-chip, no compute) between grouped layers; information diffuses across all groups over 2-3 layers. Almost certainly the cheapest translate clip: shuffle and stack, don't build a dense mix."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_11_connectivity_butterfly_monarch", "label": "Butterfly / Monarch matrices (FFT-structured mixing)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\11-connectivity.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": 